ytokine synthesis","Promotes cytokine receptor degradation","Blocks cytokine receptor expression","Increases anti-inflammatory mediators","Prevents JAK-mediated STAT protein phosphorylation"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EJAK inhibitors work by \u003Cstrong\u003Epreventing JAK-mediated STAT protein phosphorylation\u003C/strong\u003E. When cytokines bind to their receptors, they activate JAK proteins, which then phosphorylate STAT proteins. Phosphorylated STATs enter the nucleus and promote inflammatory gene transcription. By blocking JAK activity, these drugs reduce inflammatory signalling.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirectly inhibits inflammatory cytokine synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E: JAK inhibition works at the intracellular signalling level rather than affecting cytokine production\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPromotes cytokine receptor degradation\u003C/strong\u003E: JAK inhibition has no effect on receptor degradation or turnover\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocks cytokine receptor expression\u003C/strong\u003E: JAK inhibition does not affect receptor expression levels\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases anti-inflammatory mediators\u003C/strong\u003E: JAK inhibition blocks signalling pathways rather than promoting anti-inflammatory effects\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJAK inhibitors can effectively treat conditions like rheumatoid arthritis and inflammatory bowel disease where excessive cytokine signalling contributes to disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Janus kinase (JAK) inhibitors block intracellular signalling pathways that are activated by multiple cytokines.","JAK inhibitors prevent phosphorylation of Signal Transducer and Activator of Transcription (STAT) proteins, reducing inflammatory gene transcription.","JAK inhibitors are used to treat autoimmune conditions like rheumatoid arthritis and inflammatory bowel disease."],"references":["Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62902"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17053"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62902","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62902"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-06T21:31:21+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-06T21:33:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9743"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77395"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},